comment.author: 33147718@N05
comment._content: [http://www.flickr.com/photos/angeljim46] [http://www.flickr.com/photos/beachcomberaustralia] Thanks for your input folks! This one is tricky. Can't seem to find any other images detailing the two jetties. the street lamps and the fuel pumps. There is a notice on the pier that reads: 'Notice. / Sydney Harbour Trust / fishing from these jetties is strictly prohibited....By order W.E. Austin'.  EW Austin was appointed chairman to the SHT in 1930. The steam launch in the background appears to have the word 'VANILLO' or 'VANILLO' on it.
comment.authorname: Australian National Maritime Museum on The Commons

comment.author: 32162360@N00
comment._content:
Second thoughts - Bennelong Point, east side, near Man o' War steps.  The area was a mass of jetties c.1930 (pre-Opera House) - see this c.1927 map - 

[http://www.flickr.com/photos/state-records-nsw/6662642331/sizes/o/]

The "VANILLO" may be an advert on a steam vehicle ferry (see map above).
